    {
        "id": "depletion-structure-img",
        "type": "image",
        "title": "Depletion-Mode MOSFET — Physical Structure",
        "src": "/course/analog-electronics/lesson-09/depletion-mosfet-structure.jpeg",
        "caption": "(a) The depletion-mode MOSFET has a physically implanted channel (shown as the n-channel between S and D) that exists even with VGS = 0. (b) Applying negative VGS depletes the channel, reducing its width and eventually cutting off current."
